Israeli Explorers Drop as Noble Stops Leviathan 2 Drilling

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-05-15T14:08:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/israeli-gas-explorers-drop-as-noble-stops-leviathan-2-drilling.html
Ratio Oil Exploration 1992 LP (RATIL)  and
other explorers with stakes in the Leviathan natural-gas field
off Israel’s coast tumbled as drilling at the Leviathan 2 site
was stopped after water flow was found.  Ratio, which holds a 15 percent stake in the project,
dropped 6.4 percent to 0.412 shekel, the lowest level since Nov.
8, at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Avner Oil Exploration-LP
and Delek Drilling-LP, partners in the drilling site, lost 5.1
percent and 4 percent, respectively.  Noble Energy Mediterranean Ltd. notified the explorers it
decided to stop drilling at Leviathan 2 due to water flow and to
start an alternative assessment drilling at a nearby location,
the explorers said in a  statement to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange 
today.  The new drilling should start within a month and continue
for about three months at an estimated cost of $70 million,
according to the statement.  “The incident reflects the risks in these kinds of
operations and in investing in this sector,” Guil Bashan, an
analyst at the Tel Aviv-based  Israel  Brokerage & Investments
Ltd. told Bloomberg by telephone. “However, The financial
impact on the explorers seems negligent.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
